{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"rebar-debug Phase 2 (RED->GREEN) in progress:\n\nRED ORACLE CONFIRMED: tests/interfaces/store/test_txn_transient_retry.py injects 'fatal: could not parse HEAD' on the FIRST transition git commit (monkeypatching gitutil.subprocess.run) and asserts self-heal. Before any fix it FAILS with the EXACT reported error: 'rebar._errors.RebarError: rebar transition failed (exit 2): Error: git operation failed: fatal: could not parse HEAD' at _lib_writes.py:358 — same signature as CI run 29470200567. Negative test (non-transient commit failure surfaces immediately, not retried) passes. RED for the right reason.\n\nFIX (blast radius confirmed): txn.py:_git, delete.py:176, compact.py:59 ALL route through gitutil.run_git_write -> centralizing a transient retry there fixes 3 sibling families at once. event_append._git_commit/_git_commit_paths use _with_index_lock_retry directly -> covered in the same change. Test held out; fix implemented by an independent subagent from the root-cause + contract card (not the test). Design: add _with_transient_retry + _is_transient_git_error (marker 'could not parse head') to gitutil, composed as the INNER loop inside run_git_write (index.lock retry stays OUTER), mirroring the established _with_index_lock_retry + event_append transient-add-retry patterns (both tested). Next: restore held-out test, validate GREEN + mutation check (re-seed the root cause -> test back to RED)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784233432458000001,"uuid":"e2c268ce-7d0f-475f-9713-05c43dbc8a07"}